---
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";

const noteUpdated = "";

const noteExcerpt = [
  `Which brings me to the whole "New Year, New Me" thing. You've heard it before, right? It's everywhere - a season of reinvention, fresh starts, and big, shiny goals. And while I love the vibe, here's the truth I've learned over time:`,
  `You don't need January 1st to decide you want something different. Change doesn't care about the date on the calendar. It happens when you're ready to commit to it, whether it's the start of a new year or just a random Tuesday in April. Setting goals and pursuing them is less about timing and more about being honest with yourself. Too often, people get caught up in the hype, setting massive, dreamy, somewhat unrealistic resolutions (I've done it too, in the past), only to feel defeated by February.`,
];

const sidebarNotes = [
  {
    group: "Pinned",
    icon: "✎",
    title: "petty beginnings",
    date: "1/12/2025",
    preview:
      "A notes-style reading of a personal response about timing, intention, and feeling quietly called out.",
    href: "/petty-beginnings/",
    active: true,
  },
  {
    group: "Today",
    icon: "⚑",
    title: "entrepreneurship",
    date: "12/03/2025",
    preview:
      "Lessons from building Greysole and Casestody: consistency, community, momentum, and adapting when the plan changes.",
    href: "/entrepreneurship/",
    active: false,
  },
  {
    group: "Archive",
    icon: "✈️",
    title: "travel journal",
    date: "3/13/2024",
    preview: "A week between Addis Ababa and Dubai, rebuilt as a Notes-style travel diary.",
    href: "/travel-journal/",
    active: false,
  },
  {
    group: "Home",
    icon: "⌂",
    title: "back home",
    date: "4/17/2026",
    preview: "Return to the homepage and browse projects, work, and the full writing list.",
    href: "/",
    active: false,
  },
];

const articleSections = [
  { paragraphs: [
      {
        html: `It’s a new year, and while I didn’t plan to start it this way, I guess I’m starting it off on a very petty note. My dear friend Marian recently posted a <a class="highlighted-blog-link" href="https://mariangasinu.com/Blog/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">blog</a> that, on the surface, was impressive—uplifting, even. But as I read through it, I couldn’t help but feel it was a subtle jab at me—a response to something I’d shared with her about my plans for 2025.`,
      },
      "Here’s an excerpt from her post:"
    ],
  },
  {paragraphs: [
      "Now, imagine this: you share your plans with a friend—telling them how you intend to fully enjoy a ‘detty December’ and then approach the new year with renewed focus and intention. They encourage you, maybe even hype you up. Then, days later, you see a blog post that subtly shades your conversation, disguising it as advice.",
      "Well, Marian, here’s my response:",
      "The start of a new year does feel like a clean slate—a fresh beginning makes it easier to reflect on the past and plan for the future. It’s like a natural checkpoint to reassess priorities and map out plans for the future.",
      "While timing may not matter for everyone, starting on January 1st is simply a STRUCTURED AND INTENTIONAL CHOICE FOR THOSE OF US WHO THRIVE ON  PLANNING AND ORGANIZATION. It doesn’t mean we’re not serious; it’s just what works for us.",
      "So, Marian, next time you feel the urge to sub your friend in a blog post, how about just saying it to my face? 😊",
      "And to anyone reading this: whether you start fresh in January or on a random Tuesday in April, what matters most is committing to the journey when you’re ready. After all, there’s no wrong time to pursue the change you want in your life.",
    ],
  },
  { paragraphs: [
      "Sincerely,",
      "Glinder",],
  },
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Petty Beginnings | Glinder</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A Notes-style version of Glinder's Petty Beginnings post."
    />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap"
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/global.css" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --notes-window: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.84);
        --notes-sidebar: rgba(243, 243, 247, 0.92);
        --notes-pane: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);
        --notes-divider: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
        --notes-search: #e8e8ed;
        --notes-preview: #6e6e73;
        --notes-selected: #f4c542;
        --notes-selected-text: #1c1c1e;
        --notes-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
      }

      @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
        :root {
          --notes-window: rgba(49, 49, 49, 0.96);
          --notes-sidebar: rgba(54, 54, 54, 0.96);
          --notes-pane: rgba(50, 50, 50, 0.98);
          --notes-divider: rgba(232, 216, 201, 0.1);
          --notes-search: #404040;
          --notes-preview: rgba(232, 216, 201, 0.64);
          --notes-selected: #9b7c23;
          --notes-selected-text: #fff8ea;
          --notes-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.34);
        }
      }

      body {
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .notes-page {
        min-height: 100vh;
        padding: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 2rem);
      }

      .notes-shell {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(280px, 360px) minmax(0, 1fr);
        min-height: calc(100vh - clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem));
        border: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
        border-radius: 30px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--notes-window);
        box-shadow: var(--notes-shadow);
        backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
      }

      .notes-sidebar {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.25rem;
        padding: 1.35rem 1rem 1.25rem;
        background: var(--notes-sidebar);
        border-right: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
      }

      .notes-chrome {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 1rem;
        padding: 0 0.25rem;
      }

      .notes-traffic {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.65rem;
      }

      .notes-traffic a,
      .notes-traffic span {
        display: block;
        width: 0.95rem;
        height: 0.95rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
      }

      .notes-traffic a {
        background: #ff5f57;
      }

      .notes-traffic span:nth-child(2) { background: #febc2e; }
      .notes-traffic span:nth-child(3) { background: #28c840; }

      .notes-compose {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        width: 2.55rem;
        height: 2.55rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
        border-radius: 14px;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
      }

      .notes-searchbar {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.7rem;
        min-height: 3.15rem;
        padding: 0 1rem;
        border-radius: 16px;
        background: var(--notes-search);
        color: var(--notes-preview);
        font-size: 1.02rem;
      }

      .notes-searchbar span:first-child {
        font-size: 1.28rem;
        line-height: 1;
      }

      .notes-groups {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1.15rem;
      }

      .notes-group {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.65rem;
      }

      .notes-group-title {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      }

      .notes-entry {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.3rem;
        padding: 1rem 1.05rem;
        border-radius: 18px;
        color: inherit;
        background: transparent;
        border: 1px solid transparent;
        transition: background 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
      }

      .notes-entry:hover,
      .notes-entry:focus-visible {
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--notes-search) 78%, transparent);
      }

      .notes-entry-active {
        background: var(--notes-selected);
        color: var(--notes-selected-text);
      }

      .notes-entry-active .notes-entry-date,
      .notes-entry-active .notes-entry-preview {
        color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--notes-selected-text) 78%, transparent);
      }

      .notes-entry-top {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.65rem;
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .notes-entry-title {
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .notes-entry-date {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.88rem;
      }

      .notes-entry-preview {
        color: var(--notes-preview);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        line-height: 1.45;
      }

      .notes-reader {
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 3rem);
        background: var(--notes-pane);
      }

      .notes-mobile-close {
        display: none;
      }

      .notes-reader-inner {
        width: min(100%, 860px);
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .notes-reader-date {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .notes-title {
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
        line-height: 0.96;
        letter-spacing: -0.06em;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .notes-summary {
        margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      .notes-quote {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.3rem;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
        border-radius: 18px;
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--notes-search) 78%, transparent);
      }

      .notes-quote-label {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .notes-quote-text {
        margin-top: 0.65rem;
        font-size: 1.16rem;
        line-height: 1.75;
      }

      .notes-section {
        padding: 1.45rem 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
      }

      .notes-section:first-of-type {
        border-top: 0;
        padding-top: 0;
      }

      .notes-section-title {
        font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.3vw, 2rem);
        line-height: 1.08;
      }

      .notes-section-copy {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.95rem;
        margin-top: 1rem;
      }

      .notes-section-copy p {
        color: var(--fg);
        font-size: 1.16rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
      }

      .notes-section-copy :global(.highlighted-blog-link) {
        color: var(--fg);
        font-weight: 700;
        text-decoration-line: underline;
        text-decoration-thickness: 0.08em;
        text-underline-offset: 0.12em;
        transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
      }

      .notes-section-copy :global(.highlighted-blog-link:hover),
      .notes-section-copy :global(.highlighted-blog-link:focus-visible) {
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      .notes-signoff {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        padding-top: 1.35rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.96rem;
      }

      .notes-signoff a {
        color: var(--accent);
      }

      @media (max-width: 980px) {
        .notes-shell {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .notes-sidebar {
          border-right: 0;
          border-bottom: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 767px) {
        .notes-page {
          padding: 0;
        }

        .notes-shell {
          display: block;
          min-height: 100vh;
          border-radius: 0;
          border: 0;
          box-shadow: none;
        }

        .notes-reader {
          min-height: 100vh;
          padding: 1rem 1rem 2rem;
        }

        .notes-sidebar {
          display: none;
        }

        .notes-mobile-close {
          display: inline-flex;
          align-items: center;
          justify-content: center;
          min-width: 2.6rem;
          height: 2.6rem;
          margin-bottom: 1rem;
          border: 1px solid var(--notes-divider);
          border-radius: 999px;
          font-size: 1.2rem;
          line-height: 1;
        }

        .notes-reader-date {
          text-align: left;
          margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="notes-page">
      <div class="notes-shell">
        <aside class="notes-sidebar" aria-label="Notes navigation">
          <div class="notes-chrome">
            <div class="notes-traffic">
              <a href="/" aria-label="Close and go home"></a>
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
            </div>

            <span class="notes-compose" aria-hidden="true">✎</span>
          </div>

          <div class="notes-searchbar" aria-hidden="true">
            <span>⌕</span>
            <span>Search</span>
          </div>

          <div class="notes-groups">
            {Array.from(new Set(sidebarNotes.map((note) => note.group))).map((group) => (
              <section class="notes-group">
                <h2 class="notes-group-title">{group}</h2>

                {sidebarNotes
                  .filter((note) => note.group === group)
                  .map((note) => (
                    <a
                      class={`notes-entry ${note.active ? "notes-entry-active" : ""}`}
                      href={note.href}
                      target={note.href.startsWith("http") ? "_blank" : undefined}
                      rel={note.href.startsWith("http") ? "noreferrer" : undefined}
                    >
                      <div class="notes-entry-top">
                        <span aria-hidden="true">{note.icon}</span>
                        <span class="notes-entry-title">{note.title}</span>
                      </div>
                      <span class="notes-entry-date">{note.date}</span>
                      <p class="notes-entry-preview">{note.preview}</p>
                    </a>
                  ))}
              </section>
            ))}
          </div>
        </aside>

        <article class="notes-reader">
          <div class="notes-reader-inner">
            <a class="notes-mobile-close" href="/" aria-label="Close and go home">✕</a>
            <p class="notes-reader-date">{noteUpdated}</p>
            <h1 class="notes-title">petty beginnings</h1>
          

            {articleSections.map((section, index) => (
              <section class="notes-section">
                {section.title && <h2 class="notes-section-title">{section.title}</h2>}

                <div class="notes-section-copy">
                  {section.paragraphs.map((paragraph) => (
                    typeof paragraph === "string" ? <p>{paragraph}</p> : <p set:html={paragraph.html} />
                  ))}
                </div>

                {index === 0 && (
                  <section class="notes-quote">
                    <div class="notes-quote-text">
                      {noteExcerpt.map((paragraph) => (
                        <p>{paragraph}</p>
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  </section>
                )}
              </section>
            ))}

            <footer class="notes-signoff">
            </footer>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </body>
</html>
